e government of sir john a macdonald compensated it for assuming the risk of developing the railroad that bound canada from coast to coast with the subsurface rights for a checkerboard pattern of most of alberta and part of saskatchewan encana inherited these subsurface mineral rightscitation needed in  the canadian pacific railway drilled for water near medicine hat ab and discovered natural gascitation needed in  canadian pacific created canadian pacific oil and gas to manage its oil and gas properties and its mineral rightscitation needed in  canadian pacific oil and gas merged with centraldel rio oils resulting in pan canadian petroleum limitedcitation needed in  pancanadian petroleum ltd was spun out of canadian pacific limited it subsequently merged with alberta energy corporation to form encana in april  encana corporation launched operations with president and ceo gwyn morgan its initial goal was a big company that couldn’t be taken over that resulted in the disposition of producing assets in ecuador and the north sea as well as exploratory assets in chad ghana brazil australia the mackenzie delta and the middle east in spring  residents from pavillion wyoming approached the united states environmental protection agency about changes in water quality from their domestic wells in may  encana announced to split into a gas and an oil company in  the epa announced that it had found hydrocarbon contaminants in residents’ drinking water wells in pavilion wyoming in november  encana split into a company focusing on north american natural gas production representing about twothirds of the companys production and its reserves that retained the name encana and an oil company named cenovus energy in  the dow jones sustainability index included encana for the first time in november  a potential buyer backed out of buying the pavilion gas field  net earnings slumped to  million from over one billion the year before in february  mitsubishi paid approximately c billion for a  percent interest in the cutbank ridge partnership with encana which involves  net acres of montney formation natural gas lands in northeast british columbia in december  encana announced a us  billion joint venture with stateowned beijingbased petrochina through which petrochina would have received a  percent stake in encana’s duvernay formation acreage in alberta this was in line with the rules that favor minority stakes over takeovers since prime minister stephen harpers december   prohibition of purchases by stateowned enterprises seeking to invest in canadian oil sands the deal later fell flat at the end of  encanas staff had increased to  employees during  encanas cash flow decreased the company cut dividends by more than two thirds and shares fell by more than  per cent in november  it announced a restructuring plan to lay off  per cent of its employees to close its office in plano texas to sell assets and to found a separate company for its mineral rights and royalty interests across southern alberta it planned to invest three quarters of its  capital into five projects projects in the montney formation and the duvernay shale in alberta the san juan basin in new mexico louisianas tuscaloosa marine shale and the denverjulesburg basin dj basin in northeast colorado extending into wyoming and nebraska in september  encana announced that it would acquire athlon energy inc for  billion in may  jonah energy llc acquired encanas jonah field operations in sublette county wyoming from encana usa lawsuitsedit from  through  encana usa accumulated a large land position of  net acres at an average acre in the collingwoodutica shale gas play in michigans middle ordovician collingwood formationbetter source needed in may  encana had paid about  an acre for oil and gas rights on  acres  hectares at an auction by the michigan department of natural resources which was  percent less than the average paid two years ago in the area in july  reuters reported about emails between encana and chesapeake energy americas secondlargest natural gas producer to divide up michigan counties state land leases for an october  auction to suppress land prices in  a private landowner filed suit against encana and chesapeake for bid rigging justice department and michigan authorities were investigating whether state or federal laws were violated as of update the irs and sec are also still investigating in  two property owners adjacent to a drilling unit filed suit against the michigan department of environmental quality and encana oil  gas usa inc for potential harm due to proximity in october  the judge of the circuit court of ingham county issued an injunction against encana starting to drill until an administrative hearing before deqs supervisor of wells had been completed re part  of deqs rules for oil and gas operations in may  the supervisor of wells found with encana that the petitioners did not have standing because they did not own land within the drilling unit and dismissed the case in november  ecojustice the sierra club and the wilderness committee filed a lawsuit against encana corporation and the british columbias oil and gas commission for excessive water use from lakes and rivers for its hydraulic fracturing for shale gas granted by repeated shortterm water permits a violation of the provincial water act criticismedit in northeastern british columbia five explosions targeted encana pipelines between october  and january  media reports indicate the pipeline may have been bombed by a disgruntled community member fearing the sour gas containing hydrogen sulfide which can be fatal if too much of it is inhaled poses a danger to the community encanas hydraulic fracturing operations in the us are visible in the  documentary gaslandcitation needed which alleges that hydraulic fracturing causes pollution of ground and surface water as well as air and soil pollution issues were raised for the deep panuke project offshore of nova scotia when it was proposed in  as a smaller version with increased ocean discharges and when encana asked for a streamlined regulatory process without public hearings sustainabilityedit annually encana publishes a sustainability report in which they voluntarily disclose a wide variety of operational statistics including energy usage emissions intensity ghg emissions water usage flared and vented volumes reportable spills reclaimed land community investment aboriginal engagement employee education ethical controls governance practices corruption prevention activities total staff attrition gender ratios safety and recordable injuries and an independent assurance of all statistics all data is shown annually benchmarked against prior years if the metric is trending unfavorably encana details how it is addressing the issue referencesedit  a b our history encana corporation  retrieved    a b c d e encana annual report  pdf   encana shares edge lower after ceo suddenly resigns calgary ab google  october  retrieved  october    judy mckinnon encana to sell colorado oil and gas assets for  million wsj  october   a b c rebecca penty  december  encanas petrochina partnership may be first of many edmonton ab china institute university of alberta archived from the original on  december  retrieved  february    a b encana  february  annual information form pdf   a b c d encana corporation ecato reuters nd retrieved  january    joann alberstat  december  deep panuke project reaches full gas production halifax ns the chronicle herald retrieved  december    encana sells north texas natural gas assets for  million pipeline  gas journal   oildom publishing company of texas inc december    a b dj basin pdf encana april  retrieved  may    a b c d e encana laying off  of workers cbc news  november  retrieved  august    encana closes cutbank ridge deal february   retrieved  january    encana q operating profit drops  percent petro global news retrieved  march    canadian pacific railway limitedhistory inte