bsidiaries encana oil and gas usa website wwwencanacom encana corporation produces transports and markets natural gas oil and natural gas liquids ngls it was formed in  and descends from the th century canadian pacific railway and canadian pacific oil and gas in the th century respectively all of encana’s reserves and production are located in north america since other international assets were divested in the mids the corporate headquarters are in calgary alberta encana has onshore operations in alberta and northeast british columbia and a development off the coast of nova scotia in the united states encanas subsidiary operates in colorado new mexico wyoming texas and louisiana after incorporating in  encana corporation formed two subsidiaries in  with encana operating in unconventional natural gas and natural gas liquids exploration processing and transportation and an integrated oil company called cenovus energy in october  encana announced it would sell its colorado oil and gas assets for  million contents  canadian operations  us operations  production and profits  history  lawsuits  criticism  sustainability  references  external links canadian operationsedit encana is canada’s largest natural gas producer penty  china institute with a large land position in western canada of  million net acres of which about  million net acres are undeveloped encanas natural gas resource plays include bighorn in west central alberta coalbed methane cutbank ridge in northern british columbia peace river arch in northwest alberta clearwater in southern alberta including the emerging clearwater oil play and greater sierra in northeast british columbia the duvernay in west central alberta is an emerging play the deep panuke project produces and processes natural gas from approximately  kilometers offshore southeast of halifax nova scotia since  as of  december update bighorn is a  gross acres  net acres resource play in west central alberta with resthaven kakwa redrock and berland as primary properties in  encana drilled approximately  net wells and produced about  barrels per day of natural gas and approximately  barrels per day of oil and ngls cutbank ridge is in the canadian rocky mountain foothills southwest of dawson creek british columbia as of  december update encana controlled about  gross undeveloped acres  net acres over the deep basin montney formation of which  net acres have been developed since  near dawson creek at peace river arch in northwest alberta encana drills into the montney formation where it controls about  gross undeveloped acres  net acres as of  december update about  net wells produced  barrels per day of natural gas and  barrels per day of oil and ngls after royalties encana is a  owner of the sexsmith plant which has a total capacity of  barrels per day after it sold compression and gathering lines in the sexsmith and pipestone areas to an unrelated third party at the same time the gordondale sour gas deep cut plant started production with a processing capacity of  barrels per day and is expected to yield  thousand barrels per day after royalties us operationsedit encana oil  gas usa inc is the us subsidiary of encana corporation and headquartered in denver it has interest in approximately  million net acres of land in the us of which  million net acres were undeveloped as of  in december  encana closed the sale of the majority of its north texas natural gas producing properties as of update key resource plays included the haynesville shale in southwestern arkansas northwest louisiana and east texas jonah field in wyoming wattenberg gas field in the denverjulesburg basin abbreviated dj basin in northeast colorado extending into wyoming and nebraska and the piceance basin in colorado for oil interest encana amassed rights for the collingwoodutica shale michigan between  and  mostly in cheboygan kalkaska michigan and missaukee counties it also has oil interests in the san juan basin in new mexico and the tuscaloosa marine shale on the border between mississippi and louisiana by  encana usa was funding about  different plays production and profitsedit at year end  the company’s average production was  billion cubic feet per day of natural gas and  barrels per day of oil and natural gas liquids it had more than  employees per its april  prospectus since  the companys strategy has been to divest its lowprofit generating assets and focus on the lucrative core business of natural gas and liquids production on february   encana cut  million from its  budget after reporting an  percent drop in operating profits historyedit when the canadian pacific railway was formed the government of sir john a macdonald compensated it for assuming the risk of developing the railroad that bound canada from coast to coast with the subsurface rights for a checkerboard pattern of most of alberta and part of saskatchewan encana inherited these subsurface mineral rightscitation needed in  the canadian pacific railway drilled for water near medicine hat ab and discovered natural gascitation needed in  canadian pacific created canadian pacific oil and gas to manage its oil and gas properties and its mineral rightscitation needed in  canadian pacific oil and gas merged with centraldel rio oils resulting in pan canadian petroleum limitedcitation needed in  pancanadian petroleum ltd was spun out of canadian pacific limited it subsequently merged with alberta energy corporation to form encana in april  encana corporation launched operations with president and ceo gwyn morgan its initial goal was a big company that couldn’t be taken over that resulted in the disposition of producing assets in ecuador and the north sea as well as exploratory assets in chad ghana brazil australia the mackenzie delta and the middle east in spring  residents from pavillion wyoming approached the united states environmental protection agency about changes in water quality from their domestic wells in may  encana announced to split into a gas and an oil company in  the epa announced that it had found hydrocarbon contaminants in residents’ drinking water wells in pavilion wyoming in november  encana split into a company focusing on north american natural gas production representing about twothirds of the companys production and its reserves that retained the name encana and an oil company named cenovus energy in  the dow jones sustainability index included encana for the first time in november  a potential buyer backed out of buying the pavilion gas field  net earnings slumped to  million from over one billion the year before in february  mitsubishi paid approximately c billion for a  percent interest in the cutbank ridge partnership with encana which involves  net acres of montney formation natural gas lands in northeast british columbia in december  encana announced a us  billion joint venture with stateowned beijingbased petrochina through which petrochina would have received a  percent stake in encana’s duvernay formation acreage in alberta this was in line with the rules that favor minority stakes over takeovers since prime minister stephen harpers december   prohibition of purchases by stateowned enterprises seeking to invest in canadian oil sands the deal later fell flat at the end of  encanas staff had increased to  employees during  encanas cash flow decreased the company cut dividends by more than two thirds and shares fell by more than  per cent in november  it announced a restructuring plan to lay off  per cent of its employees to close its office in plano texas to sell assets and to found a separate company for its mineral rights and royalty interests across southern alberta it planned to invest three quarters of its  capital into five projects projects in the montney formation and the duvernay shale in alberta the san juan basin in new mexico louisianas tuscaloosa marine shale and the denverjulesburg basin dj basin in northeast colorado extending into wyoming and nebraska in september  encana announced that it would acquire athlon energy inc for  billion in may  jonah energy llc acquired encanas jonah field operations in sublette county wyoming from encana usa lawsuitsedit from  through  encana usa accumulated a large land position of  net acres at an average acre in the collingwoodutica shale gas play in michigans middle ordovician collingwood formationbetter source needed in may  encana had paid about  an acre for oil and gas rights on  acres  hectares at an auction by the michigan department of natural resources which was  percent less than the average paid two years ago in the area in july  reuters reported about emails between encana and chesapeake energy americas secondlargest natural gas producer to divide up michigan counties state land leases for an october  auction to suppress land prices in  a private landowner filed suit against encana and chesapeake for bid rigging justice department and michigan authorities were investigating whether state or federal laws were violated as of update the irs and sec are also still investigating in  two property owners adjacent to a drilling unit filed suit against the michigan department of environmental quality and encana oil  gas usa inc for potential harm due to proximity in october  the judge of the circuit court of ingham county issued an injunction against encana starting to drill until an administrative hearing before deqs supervisor of wells had been completed re part  of deqs rules for oil and gas operations in may  the supervisor of wells found with encana that the petitioners did not have standing because they did not own land within the drilling unit and dismissed the case in november  ecojustice the sierra club and the wilderness committee filed a lawsuit against encana corporation and the british columbias oil and gas commission for excessive water use from lakes and rivers for its hydraulic fracturing for shale gas granted by repeated shortterm water permits a violation of the provincial water act criticismedit in northeastern british columbia five explosions targeted encana pipelines between october  and january  media reports indicate the pipeline may have been bombed by a disgruntled community member fearing the sour gas containing hydrogen sulfide which can be fatal if too much of it is inhaled poses a danger to the community encanas hydraulic fracturing operations in the us are visible in the  documentary gaslandcitation needed which alleges that hydraulic fracturing causes pollution of ground and surface water as well as air and soil pollution issues were raised for the deep panuke project offshore of nova scotia when it was proposed in  as a smaller version with increased ocean discharges and when encana asked for a streamlined regulatory process without public hearings sustainabilityedit annually encana publishes a sustainability report in which they voluntarily disclose a wide variety of operational statistics including energy usage emissions intensity ghg emissions water usage flared and vented volumes reportable spills reclaimed land community investment aboriginal engagement employee education ethical controls governance practices corruption prevention activities total staff attrition gender ratios safety and recordable injuries and an independent assurance of all statistics all data is shown annually benchmarked against prior years if the metric is trending unfavorably encana details how it is addressing the issue referencesedit  a b our history encana corporation  retrieved    a b c d e encana annual report  pdf   encana shares edge lower after ceo suddenly resigns calgary ab google  october  retrieved  october    judy mckinnon encana to sell colorado oil and gas assets for  million wsj  october   a b c rebecca penty  december  encanas petrochina partnership may be first of many edmonton ab china institute university of alberta archived from the original on  december  retrieved  february    a b encana  february  annual inform